      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/result/prior-study-synthesis-result-001",
      "type": "prov:Entity",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior FEA-to-bench validation studies for spinal implant constructs",
      "description": "This entity consolidates findings from twelve prior independent FEA validation studies of spinal pedicle screw constructs published between 2008 and 2022, spanning titanium alloy screws from 5.5 mm to 8.5 mm diameter across three commercial systems. The synthesis establishes that continuum linear-elastic FEA with frictional contact consistently reproduces ASTM F1717 compression-bending QoIs within 5–8% error bounds, supporting the model form and acceptance criteria adopted in the present COU. The breadth and consistency of this prior evidence base provides strong empirical grounding for the modeling assumptions and acceptance thresholds used here."
